[
  "div",
  {
    "className": "content-wrapper"
  },
  [
    "header",
    {
      "className": "lesson-header"
    },
    [
      "p",
      {
        "className": "lesson-meta"
      },
      "Lesson 18"
    ],
    [
      "h1",
      {},
      "Degrees of Adjectives"
    ]
  ],
  [
    "article",
    {},
    [
      "section",
      {},
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "In Greek, adjectives change their form to indicate intensity. There\n            are three degrees:",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "Positive"
        ],
        " ",
        "(tall),",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "Comparative"
        ],
        " ",
        "(taller), and",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "Superlative"
        ],
        " ",
        "(tallest)."
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {},
        "1. The Positive Degree (Θετικός)"
      ],
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "This is the base form of the adjective as learned in the previous\n            lesson."
      ],
      [
        "ul",
        {
          "className": "base-list"
        },
        [
          "li",
          {},
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "greek-text"
            },
            "ωραίος"
          ],
          " ",
          "(beautiful)"
        ],
        [
          "li",
          {},
          [
            "span",
            {
              "className": "greek-text"
            },
            "καλός"
          ],
          " ",
          "(good)"
        ]
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {
          "className": "mt-12"
        },
        "2. The Comparative Degree (Συγκριτικός)"
      ],
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "There are two ways to form the comparative in Greek:"
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "comparison-grid mt-8"
        },
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "method "
          },
          [
            "h3",
            {},
            "Method A: Using \"πιο\""
          ],
          [
            "p",
            {},
            "Simply place the word",
            " ",
            [
              "strong",
              {},
              "πιο"
            ],
            " ",
            "(more) before the adjective.\n                    This works for almost all adjectives."
          ],
          [
            "div",
            {
              "className": "example-box"
            },
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "πιο ωραίος"
            ],
            " ",
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "translation"
              },
              "more beautiful / handsomer"
            ]
          ]
        ],
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "method "
          },
          [
            "h3",
            {},
            "Method B: Using Suffixes"
          ],
          [
            "p",
            {},
            "Add the suffix",
            " ",
            [
              "strong",
              {},
              "-ότερος"
            ],
            " ",
            "to the root of the adjective."
          ],
          [
            "div",
            {
              "className": "example-box"
            },
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "ωραι",
              " ",
              [
                "strong",
                {},
                "ότερος"
              ]
            ],
            " ",
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "translation"
              },
              "more beautiful"
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {
          "className": "mt-12"
        },
        "3. The Superlative Degree (Υπεθετικός)"
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "superlative-table  mt-8"
        },
        [
          "table",
          {},
          [
            "thead",
            {},
            [
              "tr",
              {},
              [
                "th",
                {},
                "Type"
              ],
              [
                "th",
                {},
                "Formation"
              ],
              [
                "th",
                {},
                "Example"
              ]
            ]
          ],
          [
            "tbody",
            {},
            [
              "tr",
              {},
              [
                "td",
                {},
                [
                  "strong",
                  {},
                  "Relative"
                ]
              ],
              [
                "td",
                {},
                "Article + \"πιο\" + Adj"
              ],
              [
                "td",
                {},
                [
                  "span",
                  {
                    "className": "greek-text"
                  },
                  "ο πιο ωραίος"
                ],
                " ",
                "(the most\n                            beautiful)"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "tr",
              {},
              [
                "td",
                {},
                [
                  "strong",
                  {},
                  "Absolute"
                ]
              ],
              [
                "td",
                {},
                "Add",
                " ",
                [
                  "strong",
                  {},
                  "-ότατος"
                ]
              ],
              [
                "td",
                {},
                [
                  "span",
                  {
                    "className": "greek-text"
                  },
                  "ωραι",
                  " ",
                  [
                    "strong",
                    {},
                    "ότατος"
                  ]
                ],
                " ",
                "(very beautiful)"
              ]
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "info-box  mt-12 mb-12"
        },
        [
          "h3",
          {},
          "Common Irregulars"
        ],
        [
          "p",
          {},
          "Some adjectives have unique comparative forms:"
        ],
        [
          "ul",
          {},
          [
            "li",
            {},
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "καλός"
            ],
            " ",
            "→",
            " ",
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "καλύτερος"
            ],
            " ",
            "(better)"
          ],
          [
            "li",
            {},
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "μεγάλος"
            ],
            " ",
            "→",
            " ",
            [
              "span",
              {
                "className": "greek-text"
              },
              "μεγαλύτερος"
            ],
            " ",
            "(bigger)"
          ]
        ]
      ]
    ]
